profile_positions.description:
MB offers generalist and specialist mental health care services delivered by a team of professionals, helping people to deal with psychological problems that hinder their daily lives. 

Responsibilities:
- The CPO will have the mandate to set bold HR initiatives aligning the Human Resources agenda with the strategic direction of the company;
- Works on cultural transformation, organizational development, and talent management, and responsible for developing HR initiatives that are linked to the overall vision and business objectives of the company; 
- The CPO is an exceptional leader, who will further develop the culture and the organization to achieve the strategic goals of the company. Act as a critical and active member of the Board, contribute expertise, insight and leadership to MB and its success;
- Serving as senior advisor providing vision and leadership to support in achieving its mission, goals, and objectives helping to ensure that the company will be transformed and grows the business;
- Develop and integrate tools, processes, and initiatives to increase the employee engagement rate;
- Develop and implement / enhance a talent strategy (career development, leadership development, early talent identification, performance management);
- Develop and enhance a clear, compelling, and consistent Employee Value Proposition;
- Ensure technology and systems (HRIS) and HR data are in place and effective;
- Guide, inspire and mentor the HR team, which consists of 21 colleagues;
- Translate HR data into specialized advice to pro-actively steer and guide the Board into the right change initiatives;
- Ensure a strong results orientation & embed an environment where everyone feels valued and respected. End responsible for the necessary governance relating to HR issues where required.

Backbase is a fast growing fintech software provider that empowers financial institutions to accelerate their digital transformation and effectively compete in a digital-first world. 
Backbase has 1000 employees worldwide with headquarters in Amsterdam (HQ Global) and Atlanta (HQ Americas) and operations in London, Cardiff, Toronto, New York, Boise, Krakaw, Tokyo and Singapore.

Responsibilities:
- Able to act as strategic business partner and experienced in topics like organizational design, performance management, diversity and inclusion, compensation and rewards, coaching and development;
- Organise the right leadership and support for employees and managers in Covid Times;
- Develop and execute a global HR vision, mission and strategy;
- To restructure the HR Organization and position HR on the right level to support the business to reach their goals;
- Guide, inspire and mentor the HR team which consists of 11 colleagues;
- Give HR advice on perm, temp and remote staff worldwide;
- Guide the HR aspects of global expansion to new office locations;
- Lead and advice on Compensation & Benefits topics like pensions, employee insurance, WGA-ERD etc.
- Focus on employee retention and employee experience programs (e.g. Training & Development);
- Work cross functionally to help Backbase scale quickly and efficiently without unnecessarily relying on process and rules to achieve this goal;
- Exposure to employment regulations across countries and while not being the expert outside of Dutch Law, knowing the right questions to ask at the right time;
- Opening up new offices and employ employees in Japan, Mexico, Poland, Germany and India;
- TMS / HRMS: Digization of HRM Tools for Talent & Performance, Survey and Compensation. Goal : To support all employees, managers and HR worldwide in the best possible way by using the proper tools.
